<table class="infobox" style="width:22em"><caption>Blacksmith</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Kov%C3%A1%C5%99_p%C5%99i_pr%C3%A1ci_(Velikono%C4%8Dn%C3%AD_trhy_na_V%C3%A1clavsk%C3%A9m_n%C3%A1m%C4%9Bst%C3%AD)_055.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Kovář při práci (Velikonoční trhy na Václavském náměstí) 055.jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Kov%C3%A1%C5%99_p%C5%99i_pr%C3%A1ci_%28Velikono%C4%8Dn%C3%AD_trhy_na_V%C3%A1clavsk%C3%A9m_n%C3%A1m%C4%9Bst%C3%AD%29_055.jpg/250px-Kov%C3%A1%C5%99_p%C5%99i_pr%C3%A1ci_%28Velikono%C4%8Dn%C3%AD_trhy_na_V%C3%A1clavsk%C3%A9m_n%C3%A1m%C4%9Bst%C3%AD%29_055.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="250" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Kov%C3%A1%C5%99_p%C5%99i_pr%C3%A1ci_%28Velikono%C4%8Dn%C3%AD_trhy_na_V%C3%A1clavsk%C3%A9m_n%C3%A1m%C4%9Bst%C3%AD%29_055.jpg/375px-Kov%C3%A1%C5%99_p%C5%99i_pr%C3%A1ci_%28Velikono%C4%8Dn%C3%AD_trhy_na_V%C3%A1clavsk%C3%A9m_n%C3%A1m%C4%9Bst%C3%AD%29_055.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Kov%C3%A1%C5%99_p%C5%99i_pr%C3%A1ci_%28Velikono%C4%8Dn%C3%AD_trhy_na_V%C3%A1clavsk%C3%A9m_n%C3%A1m%C4%9Bst%C3%AD%29_055.jpg/500px-Kov%C3%A1%C5%99_p%C5%99i_pr%C3%A1ci_%28Velikono%C4%8Dn%C3%AD_trhy_na_V%C3%A1clavsk%C3%A9m_n%C3%A1m%C4%9Bst%C3%AD%29_055.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2586" data-file-height="2584" /></a><div>A modern blacksmith exhibiting at a market stall</div></td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center">Occupation</th></tr><tr><th scope="row"><div style="display:inline-block; padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;">Occupation type</div></th><td><a href="/wiki/Profession" title="Profession">Profession</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><div style="display:inline-block; padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;">Activity sectors</div></th><td><a href="/wiki/Vocation" title="Vocation">Vocation</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center">Description</th></tr><tr><th scope="row">Competencies</th><td>Physical strength, conceptualization</td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><div style="display:inline-block; padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;">Fields of<br />employment</div></th><td>Artist, Craftsman</td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><div style="display:inline-block; padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;">Related jobs</div></th><td><a href="/wiki/Farrier" title="Farrier">Farrier</a></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>A <b>blacksmith</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Metalsmith" title="Metalsmith">metalsmith</a> who creates objects from <a href="/wiki/Wrought_iron" title="Wrought iron">wrought iron</a> or <a href="/wiki/Steel" title="Steel">steel</a> by <a href="/wiki/Forging" title="Forging">forging</a> the metal, using tools to hammer, bend, and cut (cf. <a href="/wiki/Tinsmith" title="Tinsmith">tinsmith</a>). Blacksmiths produce objects such as gates, grilles, railings, light fixtures, furniture, sculpture, tools, agricultural implements, decorative and religious items, cooking utensils and weapons. There was an historical opposition between the heavy work of the blacksmith and the more delicate operation of a <a href="/wiki/Whitesmith" title="Whitesmith">whitesmith</a>, who usually worked in gold, silver, pewter, or the finishing steps of fine steel.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The place where a blacksmith works is called variously a smithy, a forge or a blacksmith's shop.
</p><p>While there are many people who work with metal such as <a href="/wiki/Farrier" title="Farrier">farriers</a>, <a href="/wiki/Wheelwright" title="Wheelwright">wheelwrights</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Armourer" title="Armourer">armorers</a>, in former times the blacksmith had a general knowledge of how to make and repair many things, from the most complex of weapons and armor to simple things like nails or lengths of chain.
</p>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Belgique_-_Bruxelles_-_Monument_%C3%A0_John_Cockerill_-_08.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Belgique_-_Bruxelles_-_Monument_%C3%A0_John_Cockerill_-_08.jpg/220px-Belgique_-_Bruxelles_-_Monument_%C3%A0_John_Cockerill_-_08.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="330" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Belgique_-_Bruxelles_-_Monument_%C3%A0_John_Cockerill_-_08.jpg/330px-Belgique_-_Bruxelles_-_Monument_%C3%A0_John_Cockerill_-_08.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Belgique_-_Bruxelles_-_Monument_%C3%A0_John_Cockerill_-_08.jpg/440px-Belgique_-_Bruxelles_-_Monument_%C3%A0_John_Cockerill_-_08.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3528" data-file-height="5292" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Belgique_-_Bruxelles_-_Monument_%C3%A0_John_Cockerill_-_08.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div><div style="text-align:center">Statue of a blacksmith (Monument to John Cockerill in Brussels).</div></div></div></div>
